 that shall Never Die\n | magazine=[[Boys' Life]]\n | pages = 7, 35\n | publisher = Boy Scouts of America\n | issn = 0006-8608\n }}\n\n==Notes==\n'''Footnotes'''\n{{reflist|group=n}}\n\n'''Source notes'''\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n* This article incorporates public domain material from a 1906 biography of Major Burnham: {{cite book | last = Davis | first = Richard Harding |authorlink=Richard Harding Davis | title = Real Soldiers of Fortune | publisher=Charles Scribner's Sons | year = 1906 | location = New York | isbn = 978-0-87364-239-2| title-link = s:Real Soldiers of Fortune/Chapter 6 }}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n* {{cite book |ref={{sfnRef |Baden-Powell |1899}} |last=Baden-Powell |first=Robert |authorlink=Robert Baden-Powell, 1st Baron Baden-Powell |title=Aids to scouting for N.-C.Os. & men |publisher=Gale & Polden |date=1899 |location=London |oclc=316520848}}\n* {{cite book |ref={{sfnRef |Baden-Powell |1884}} |last=Baden-Powell |first=Robert |authorlink=Robert Baden-Powell, 1st Baron Baden-Powell |title=Reconnaissance and scouting. A practical course of instruction, in twenty plain lessons, for officers, non-commissioned officers, and men |publisher=W. Clowes and Sons |date=1884 |location=London |oclc=9913678}}\n* {{cite book |ref={{sfnRef |Baden-Powell |1908}} |last=Baden-Powell |first=Robert |authorlink=Robert Baden-Powell, 1st Baron Baden-Powell |title=Scouting for Boys: A Handbook for Instruction in Good Citizenship |publisher=H. Cox |date=1908 |location=London\n |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qgFcKf69L6wC |isbn=978-0-486-45719-2}}\n* {{cite book |ref={{sfnRef |Barnes |1990}} |date=1990 |last=Barnes |first=John |title=Filming the Boer War |series=Beginnings of the Cinema in England, 1894\u20131901, v. 4 |location=London |publisher=Bishopgate |isbn=978-1-85219-046-0 }}\n* {{cite journal |ref={{sfnRef |Barrett |Valiance |1999}} |last1=Barrett |first1=Cathy J. |last2=Valiance |first2=Heather |title=The Wild West Show: Socio-historic Spectacle and C