es |1926}} |title=Chief of Scouts Major Burnham's Adventures |newspaper=The Times |location=London |date=December 9, 1926 |issue=44450}}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |The Times |1899}} |title=Classified Advertising |newspaper=The Times |location=London |date=April 29, 1899}}\n* {{cite journal |ref={{sfnRef |Lloyd's |1899}} |title=Death of a Rhodesian Pioneer |date=October 1, 1899 |url=http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Death_of_a_Rhodesian_Pioneer\n |journal=[[Lloyd's Weekly Newspaper]] }}\n* {{cite web |ref={{sfnRef |laedc |2010}} |title=Dominguez Oil Field Redevelopment: Exploration and Production |date=2010 |url=http://laedc.org/reports/EconomicImpactofOilFieldRedevelopment_FINAL.pdf |publisher=Los Angeles County Economic Development Corporation |accessdate=August 29, 2013}}\n* {{cite web|ref={{sfnRef |FBI |2013}} |title=The Duquesne Spy Ring |publisher=Federal Bureau of Investigation |url=https://www.fbi.gov/about-us/history/famous-cases/the-duquesne-spy-ring |accessdate=June 12, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130930091931/http://www.fbi.gov/about-us/history/famous-cases/the-duquesne-spy-ring |archivedate=September 30, 2013 |df=mdy }}\n* {{cite journal |ref={{sfnRef |New York Evangelist |1855}} |date=April 11, 1855 |title=Ecclesiastical and Clerical |journal=New York Evangelist |volume=26 |issue=15}}.\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |London Chronicle |1901}} |date=May 5, 1901 |title=England's American Scout |newspaper=New York Times via London Chronicle |issn=0362-4331 |url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1901/05/05/101072746.pdf |accessdate=June 22, 2013 }}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |New York Times |1917}} |title=Enroll Westerners for Service in War; Movement to Register Men of That Region Begun at the Rocky Mountain Club. Headed by Major Burnham. John Hays Hammond and Others of Prominence Reported to be Supporting Plan |newspaper=New York Times |date=March 13, 1917 |url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/191