oductions.com/BoerWar_Museum/Boer90i_pastdis_burnham.html |archivedate=March 12, 2007}}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |New York Times |1912}} |date=April 23, 1912 |title=Guarding Morgan Mines: Burnham's Force also at Guggenheim Properties is report |newspaper=New York Times |issn=0362-4331 |url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1912/04/23/104847498.pdf |accessdate=September 28, 2007 }}\n* {{cite book |ref={{sfnRef |Boy Scouts of America |1933}} |title=Handbook for Boys |date=1933 |edition=3rd |publisher=Boy Scouts of America |location=New Brunswick, NJ}}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |New York Times |1896}} |date=June 25, 1896 |title=Killed the Matabele God: Burnham, the American Scout, May End Uprising |newspaper=New York Times |issn=0093-1179 |url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1896/06/25/108240032.pdf |accessdate=June 26, 2013 }}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |London Gazette |1899}} |title=London Gazette |url=http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/27146/pages/8541 |newspaper=London Gazette |issue=27146 |page=8541 |date=December 22, 1899 |location=London |publisher=T. Neuman | issn=0374-3721 |accessdate=June 14, 2013}}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |Los Angeles Times |1929}} |date=May 14, 1929 |title=Maj. Burnham and Family Depart for Africa: Angelenos to Tour World |newspaper=The Los Angeles Times |issn=0458-3035}}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |New York Times |1910}} |title=May Import African Animals to Solve Meat Problem |newspaper=New York Times |date=April 17, 1910 |url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1910/04/17/102038177.pdf |accessdate=September 28, 2007 }}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |New York Times |1901}} |date=September 28, 1901 |title=More South African Honors: Lady Sarah Wilson and Major Burnham, the American Scout, among those decorated |newspaper=New York Times |issn=0362-4331 |url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1901/09/28/117974532.pdf |accessdate=June 29, 2013 }}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |Daily Mail |1909}} |date=October 16, 1909 |title=Mr. Taft's Peril; Reported Plot to Kill Two Presidents |newspaper=Daily Mail |location=London |issn=0307-7578}}\n* {{cite web|ref={{sfnRef |Library of Congress |2009}} |title=NAACP Founder Charles Edward Russell |url=http://myloc.gov/Exhibitions/naacp/earlyyears/ExhibitObjects/CharlesEdwardRussell.aspx |publisher=Library of Congress |accessdate=August 11, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130524175716/http://myloc.gov/Exhibitions/naacp/earlyyears/ExhibitObjects/CharlesEdwardRussell.aspx |archivedate=May 24, 2013 }}\n* {{cite web |ref={{sfnRef |United States Army |2004}} |date=2004 |title=NCO and Soldier of the Year Competition: 2003 Winners |publisher=United States Army |url=http://www.army.mil/leaders/SMA/NCOandSOY/default.htm |accessdate=June 19, 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060419042009/http://www.army.mil/leaders/SMA/NCOandSOY/default.htm |archivedate=April 19, 2006}}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |New York Times |1901a}} |date=August 12, 1901 |title=A New Eldorado: Discoveries in West Africa by Major Burnham, England's American Scout |newspaper=New York Times (London Mail) |issn=0362-4331 |url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1901/08/12/101079510.pdf }}\n* {{cite web |ref={{sfnRef |LDSfilm |2004}} |title=On My Honor |url=http://www.ldsfilm.com/announced/OnMyHonor.html |publisher=LDSfilm\n |date=August 18, 2004 |accessdate=June 25, 2013}}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |The Western Times |1905}} |date=October 4, 1905 |title=Pathetic Loss | newspaper=The Western Times |location=Exeter, England |issue=17550}}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |Illustrated London News |1902}} |title=Personal |url=http://find.galegroup.com/iln/infomark.do?&source=gale&prodId=ILN&userGroupName=loc_main&tabID=T003&docPage=article&docId=HN3100473378&type=multipage&contentSet=LTO&version=1.0 |newspaper=Illustrated London News |location=London |date=January 11, 1902 |issue=3273 |accessdate=August 30, 2012}}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |New York Times |1932}} |title=Plane Line Saves Weeks: American Air Service in Guatemala Carries Odd Passenger List over Hard Country |newspaper=New York Times |date=January 17, 1932 |issn=0362-4331}}\n* {{cite web |ref={{sfnRef |Pulitzer |2013}} |title=The Pulitzer Prizes |url=http://www.pulitzer.org/awards/1928 |publisher=The Pulitzer Prizes \u2013 Columbia University |date=2013 |accessdate=August 11, 2013}}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |Atlanta Constitution |1896}} |date=November 21, 1896 |title=Rider Haggard's Tribute |newspaper=Atlanta Constitution |issn=0093-1179}}\n* {{cite book |ref={{sfnRef |International News Service |1915}} |title=Press Reference Library: Notables of the West |publisher=International News Service |location=New York |date=1915 |oclc=5532411}}\n* {{cite journal |ref={{sfnRef |Scientific Notes and News |1930}} |date=May 23, 1930 |title=Scientific Notes and News |journal=[[Science (Journal)|Science]] |issue=1847 |pages=533\u2013536 |issn=0036-8075 |volume=71 |doi=10.1126/science.71.1847.533 |jstor=1655718|bibcode=1930Sci....71..533. |url=https://zenodo.org/record/1974994 }}\n* {{cite journal |ref={{sfnRef |Southern Africa |1973}} |date=1973 |title=Film |journal=Southern Africa |volume=6 |issn=0038-3775 |author=Southern Africa Committee |oclc=1781212}}\n* {{cite web |ref={{sfnRef |Boy Scouts of America |2012}} |date=2012 |title=Silver Buffalo Award Winners 1939\u20131930 |url=http://www.scouting.org/scoutsource/Awards/SilverBuffalo/Previouswinners/1939-1930.aspx |publisher=Boy Scouts of America |accessdate=June 23, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120928061509/http://www.scouting.org/scoutsource/Awards/SilverBuffalo/Previouswinners/1939-1930.aspx |archive-date=September 28, 2012 |url-status=dead }}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |Los Angeles Times |1900}} |date=August 4, 1900 |title=Southern California by Towns and Counties: Fred Burnham now a Major in British Army; Recovering from His Injuries |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |location=Los Angeles |publisher=Times-Mirror Co. |issn=0458-3035}}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |The Times |May 9, 1899}} |date=May 9, 1899 |title=Railway And Other Companies: Northern Territories (B.S.A.) Exploring Company Limited |newspaper=[[The Times]] |issue=35824 |location=London |publisher=R. Nutkins |issn=0140-0460}}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |New York Times |1917}} |title=Roosevelt's Army Has Not Lost Hope; Colonel's Aids from All over the Country Meet and Leave the Future in His Hands |newspaper=New York Times |date=May 20, 1917 |url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1917/05/20/102345473.pdf |issn=0362-4331 }}\n* {{cite web |ref={{sfnRef |1st Lacock Scout Group |2013}} |date=2013 |title=Scouting History |url=http://1stlacockscouts.weebly.com/scouting-history.html |publisher=1st Lacock Scout Group |accessdate=July 21, 2013}}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |New York Times |1917b}} |title=Will Not Send Roosevelt; Wilson Not to Avail Himself of Volunteer Authority at Present |newspaper=New York Times |date=May 19, 1917 |issn=0362-4331}}\n* {{cite news |ref={{sfnRef |Los Angeles Times |1896a}} |date=June 6, 1896 |title=A Young South African |newspaper=The Los Angeles Times |issn=0458-3035}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Sister project links |commons=Frederick Russell Burnham|q=Frederick Russell Burnham|d=Q458036|b=no|n=no|s=Author:Frederick Russell Burnham|v=no|wikt=no}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060509215343/http://www.pinetreeweb.com/burnham.htm Major Burnham on Pine Tree Web Scouting site]\n* ''[https://web.archive.org/web/20071107054822/http://www.nmnh.si.edu/naa/guide/hsfa_africa.htm Burnham Footage of Southern and Eastern Africa]'', 35 min. silent b&w video. Footage shot in South Africa, Rhodesia and eastern Africa during a family trip. [[Smithsonian Institution]] archives. call# 85.4.1; AF-85.4.1 (1929)\n* {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060910101923/http://mssa.library.yale.edu/findaids/stream.php?xmlfile=mssa.ms.0115.xml |date=September 10, 2006 |title=Frederick Russell Burnham Papers. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University }}. A large collection of Burnham's documents: Correspondence, 1864\u20131947. Subject Files, 1890\u20131947. Writings, 1893\u20131946. Personal and Family Papers, 1879\u20131951. Photographs, ca. 1893\u20131924.\n* [http://www.oac.cdlib.org/findaid/ark:/13030/tf6n39n86s Frederick Russell Burnham Papers, 1879\u20131979, Hoover Institution Library and Archives, Stanford University.] Another large collection of Burnham's documents: Correspondence, speeches and writings, clippings, other printed matter, photographs, and memorabilia, relating to the Matabele Wars of 1893 and 1896 in Rhodesia, the Second Boer War, exploration expeditions in Africa, and gold mining in Alaska during the Klondike gold rush.\n* {{IMDb title|id=1991113|title=Major Wilson's Last Stand}}\n* {{IMDb title|id=0367031|title=Shangani Patrol}}\n\n{{Scouting|founders}}\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Scouting}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Burnham, Frederick Russell}}\n[[Category:1861 births]]\n[[Category:1947 deaths]]\n[[Category:American activists]]\n[[Category:American explorers]]\n[[Category:American mercenaries]]\n[[Category:American pioneers]]\n[[Category:Cowboys]]\n[[Category:Apache Wars]]\n[[Category:British colonial army officers]]\n[[Category:British military personnel of the Second Boer War]]\n[[Category:Companions of the Distinguished Service Order]]\n[[Category:Military snipers]]\n[[Category:People from Bulawayo]]\n[[Category:People from Mankato, Minnesota]]\n[[Category:People from Santa Barbara, California]]\n[[Category:People from the Municipality of Skagway Borough, Alaska]]\n[[Category:People of the First Matabele War]]\n[[Category:People of the Klondike Gold Rush]]\n[[Category:People of the Second Matabele War]]\n[[Category:Scouting pioneers]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Silver Buffalo Award]]\n", "name_user": "I drea